<title>SOUTH AFRICA: ROADCORP ISSUE RAISES 44.71 MILLION RAND.</title>
<headline>ROADCORP ISSUE RAISES 44.71 MILLION RAND.</headline>
<dateline>JOHANNESBURG 1997-07-04</dateline>
<text>
<p>South Africa's Roadcorp Ltd said on Friday it had raised 44.71 million rand by the issue of 23.53 million new shares at a price of 190 cents each.</p>
<p>The firm said the cash would be used to retire a subtantial part of the interest bearing debt of the firm, to redeem its &quot;B&quot; preference shares at 100 cents each and to fund organic growth by expanding locally and internationally.</p>
<p>-- Johannesburg newsroom +27 11 482 1003</p>
